findings.hepatobiliary: The liver demonstrates homogenous attenuation throughout. There is no evidence of focal lesions or biliary dilatation. The gallbladder is within normal limits.
findings.pancreas: The pancreas has normal attenuation throughout, without evidence of focal lesions or pancreatic ductal dilatation.
findings.spleen: The spleen shows normal size and attenuation throughout, without evidence of focal lesions.
findings.adrenals: The right and left adrenal glands are normal in size and shape.
findings.urinary: The kidneys are of normal and symmetric size with normal nephrogram. Subcentimeter hypodense lesion in the left upper pole likely represents a renal cyst.
findings.gastrointestinal: The appendix is hyperemic with thickened walls measuring 1.0 cm in diameter and with mild adjacent stranding consistent with acute uncomplicated appendicitis.
findings.pelvis: The urinary bladder and distal ureters are unremarkable. There is trace free fluid in the pelvis.
findings.reproductive organs: The prostate and seminal vesicles are normal.
findings.lymph nodes: There is no retroperitoneal or mesenteric lymphadenopathy.
findings.vascular: There is no abdominal aortic aneurysm or atherosclerotic disease.
findings.bones: There is no evidence of worrisome osseous lesions or acute fracture.
findings.soft tissues: The abdominal and pelvic wall is within normal limits.
